I have sad news to share. My sweet angel mother unexpectedly passed away in her sleep last night. If you didn’t know, she adopted 10 children, cared for almost 500 foster children, and owned 3 daycare centers. She spent her whole life taking care of others. I miss her so much already but I know she is still trying to take care of her kids somehow and doesn’t want us to be sad. She left an incredible legacy and I know she will not be forgotten. Love you Mama. Thank you for choosing me.

It has been one month since my mom passed away. It was sudden and unexpected and I am still trying to process it. However, I know she is still taking care of me from heaven. Being adopted, I have always wondered about where I came from. A week after my mom passed, my biological family was placed in my life for the first time. I got to meet my Aunty Sue last week and learn so much about my family, my ancestors, and our Hawaiian culture. I enjoyed being with her so much, and I have a lot more family to meet in Hawaii too. I feel so connected to my roots now and I am so grateful for my ohana ❤️

It’s my first Mother’s Day without my mom. And it’s so hard. Even harder than I expected. 

But it’s my mom’s first Mother’s Day with her own mom in a very long time. And it’s also my brother Scott’s first Mother’s Day reunited with our mom. She also gets to be with all her siblings again. And although I will be fluctuating between being happy and sad today, I am trying to focus on the positive of her passing and imagine they are all having a lovely time together ❤️ 

I remember being a kid and giving my mom artwork, cards and poems on Mother’s Day. Breakfast in bed with a little flower in a vase. And snuggling up to her and just enjoying being in her presence. Sitting at church next to her and playing with her hands. Mom, I miss your presence but I know you are having the best time. Your family loves you so much and your example of motherhood is unforgettable. 

This is also the first Mother’s Day since I recently found some of my biological family for the first time. I have learned so much about my biological mom, and she has now become a real person that I think of. She is someone I am thinking about today too ❤️

Happy Mother’s Day!
Playing hooky in New York, March 2023.

This year has truly been an emotional whirlwind. It’s been 6 months since I lost my mom, and I know it will never be okay that she’s gone. But sometimes the sun peeks out on the stormiest of days. I could never have expected what would happen right after her passing. With incredible timing, my biological family was placed in my life for the first time.

In May I went to Oahu to meet my bio family. While my bio parents’ whereabouts are unknown, I was able to meet my aunts, uncles, and cousins. It feels impossible to put these emotions into words, but I will say it was quite surreal. I had so many pinch-me moments. I was overwhelmed with joy; my heart and soul were filled with gratitude and belonging. I learned so much about my ancestors and our Hawaiian culture, but the aloha I felt from my family was even more amazing. I absolutely loved meeting everyone, and I felt so lucky to get to spend that special week with my Aunty Sue. I felt so rooted, connected, embraced, and truly honored. 

I have always felt a sacred pull in my heart to spend time on that beautiful island. I can hardly explain the special feeling of belonging I have always had when I’m there, or that draw I have always felt to return. I dreamt of taking my kids there to teach them about their heritage, and fortunately we were able to do that a few years ago. And all of a sudden, it all makes so much sense why I have felt so much at home there. My heart knew. I am so glad it found its way back, and to my ohana ❤️

Hey hey hey stop scrolling because you don’t want to miss this! @heyjennking and I are putting together a fitness event fundraiser to raise funds for those that lost everything in the devastating fire in Maui, and we need you there!! Mark your calendars for Friday September 8th for a fun filled night of 30 min: UpBeat Barre, High Fitness, and High Yo. Doors open at 7pm and class will be at 7:30-9pm. We will have treats and raffle prizes and you will see some of your favorite local instructors too like @fit.with.courtney @true.body.fitness @upbeatbarre_corona. Tickets are a $25 donation and all proceeds will go to The Maui Food Bank.

Thank you all so much and we can’t wait to Move for Maui! Deets on next slide.

Grab your bestie and join us for a night out with friends doing all your favorite workouts for a good cause! 

When: Friday September 8th 

Time: doors open at 7pm and workout starts at 7:30pm. Bring water, wear tennis shoes, and a mat. 

Where: LDS Church Building 1510 Taber St. Corona 

We will do 30min each of High Fitness, UpBeat Barre, and High Yo. Treats to follow. 

Venmo @jennrocket (Jenn King) $25 ticket donation to reserve your spot or to donate if you can’t go. Please note “Move for Maui” and all proceeds will be given to the Maui Food Bank. 

We are passionate about helping others and want to do our part to help these families out there that were left with nothing, and still need our support. No amount is too small. Your donation matters even if it’s $1. When we unite our efforts, we can make a bigger impact for good. We love you guys and appreciate your big hearts and willingness to give. 🫶🏼

I know I’ve said it a million times, but I’m going to say it again…there’s nothing better than this community right here!!! We were able to raise over $1K for the Maui Food Bank which will provide over 4 THOUSAND meals to those in need!!!! 🙌🏼

Huge shout out to all our vendors who generously donated to this cause. Please go give them a follow:
@linxbyb @readyfitgo_corona @elsinore_nutrishop @trueluxebathandbody @noellesthetics @alfredosautoglassllc @thetanningchick @hack_yourhealth_aesthetics @mrjuiceguy951 @sagapofoods @thedailycrumbl @dotdotsmile 

My heart could not be more full. A great night surrounded by amazing friends, with good music, and yummy treats; all there to make a difference in this world. That is special, and I want to thank everyone who donated. Together we were able to make a huge impact for good. 🫶🏼

This year has been insane. It started out rocky but some amazing things happened. My mom passed away…then I found my bio family in Oahu. I also got to visit New York & Paris this year. And my girlfriends just surprised me with a birthday weekend away. My children are getting older and so am I. I have done a lot and I still have a lot to do. It feels like the older you get, the bigger and better perspective you have on life. I’m just trying to hold on to every moment ✨
